The company achieved significant margin expansion and double-digit EPS growth for the year, exceeding medium-term commitments despite a soft macro environment. 3M projects continued organic sales growth of approximately 3% for 2026, driven by commercial excellence, new product launches, and operational improvements.

articles.headline: The J. M. Smucker Company $SJM Shares Acquired by Vest Financial LLC
articles.summary: Vest Financial LLC increased its stake in The J. M. Smucker Company (SJM) by 11.1% in the third quarter, bringing its total ownership to 504,715 shares valued at approximately $54.8 million. The company recently reported quarterly earnings where EPS of $2.10 missed estimates by $0.02, though revenue grew by 2.6% year-over-year. J. M. Smucker also announced a quarterly dividend of $1.10, yielding 4.3%, and analysts currently hold a consensus "Hold" rating with an average target price of $114.93.

articles.headline: BOK Financial Corporation (NASDAQ:BOKF) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
articles.summary: BOK Financial Corporation (NASDAQ:BOKF) reported record high earnings for Q4 and full-year 2025, with EPS of $2.89 and $9.17 respectively, significantly beating expectations. The company highlighted strong, broad-based loan growth of 6.4% for the year, expanded net interest margin in every quarter, and robust fee income contributing 38% of total revenue. BOK Financial maintains excellent credit quality and robust capital levels, actively returning value to shareholders through share repurchases.

articles.headline: Vest Financial LLC Has $54.89 Million Position in PulteGroup, Inc. $PHM
articles.summary: Vest Financial LLC increased its stake in PulteGroup, Inc. by 13.7% in Q3, owning 415,405 shares valued at approximately $54.89 million. PulteGroup (NYSE:PHM) exceeded Q3 earnings expectations, reporting strong revenue and net margin, and has a "Moderate Buy" consensus rating from analysts with a target price of $138.85. The company also announced an increase in its quarterly dividend to $0.26 per share.

articles.headline: D.R. Horton, Inc. (NYSE:DHI) Q1 2026 Earnings Call Transcript
articles.summary: D.R. Horton, Inc. (NYSE: DHI) reported Q1 2026 earnings, exceeding expectations with an EPS of $2.03 on $6.9 billion in revenues. The company's net sales orders increased 3% year-over-year, driven by strategic use of incentives to address affordability concerns, particularly for first-time homebuyers who made up 64% of mortgage closings. Despite elevated incentives and a projected dip in Q2 gross margins, D.R. Horton reiterated its full-year fiscal 2026 guidance for consolidated revenues and home closings, emphasizing its disciplined capital allocation, strong balance sheet, and focus on providing affordable housing opportunities.

articles.headline: Joel Isaacson & Co. LLC Has $2.57 Million Holdings in Lockheed Martin Corporation $LMT
articles.summary: Joel Isaacson & Co. LLC significantly increased its stake in Lockheed Martin Corporation by 347.2% in the third quarter, bringing their total holdings to $2.57 million. Other institutional investors also adjusted their positions, and a corporate insider, COO John Frank A. St, sold a substantial portion of his shares. Analysts have a mixed view on LMT, with a current average rating of "Hold" and a price target of $543.82.

articles.headline: Vest Financial LLC Lowers Holdings in General Dynamics Corporation $GD
articles.summary: Vest Financial LLC reduced its stake in General Dynamics Corporation by 13.1% in the third quarter of last year, selling 26,366 shares and retaining 175,424 shares valued at $59.82 million. This move comes as other hedge funds have adjusted their positions in the aerospace company. General Dynamics recently exceeded quarterly earnings expectations and announced a quarterly dividend of $1.50 per share, with analysts currently rating the stock as a "Moderate Buy."

articles.headline: Vest Financial LLC Sells 148,833 Shares of Stanley Black & Decker, Inc. $SWK
articles.summary: Vest Financial LLC reduced its stake in Stanley Black & Decker (SWK) by 16.5% in Q3, selling 148,833 shares and retaining 754,330 shares valued at $56.07 million. Despite institutional selling, other large investors increased their holdings. Wall Street analysts currently rate SWK as a "Hold" with an average target price of $87.33, and the company recently announced a quarterly dividend yielding 4.1%.

articles.headline: Wells Fargo Reaffirms Their Hold Rating on Pool (POOL)
articles.summary: Wells Fargo analyst Sam Reid has reaffirmed a Hold rating on Pool (NASDAQ: POOL) with a price target of $250.00, despite the stock closing higher at $267.99. This comes amidst negative corporate insider sentiment, with 31 insiders selling shares recently, including the CEO. Goldman Sachs, however, recently maintained a Buy rating on POOL, though they lowered their price target to $310 from $360.

articles.headline: DuPont to detail 2025 results in Feb. 10 earnings call
articles.summary: DuPont (NYSE: DD) announced it will release its fourth quarter and full year 2025 financial results on February 10, 2026, at 6:00 a.m. ET, followed by a conference call at 8:00 a.m. ET. The event will be webcast live on the company's investor relations website. The announcement includes detailed dial-in information and highlights of recent company history and market performance.

articles.headline: 2 Industrial Mutual Funds to Grab as Cyclical Tailwinds Build
articles.summary: U.S. industrial stocks are off to a strong start in 2026 due to improving activity data and renewed investor interest in cyclical sectors, with the Industrial Select Sector SPDR Fund (XLI) gaining 5.4% year-to-date. This performance is supported by resilient industrial operations, structural themes like reshoring and infrastructure spending, and a shift in investor preferences toward more reasonably priced industrial stocks. The article recommends two Zacks Rank #2 industrial mutual funds, Fidelity Select Materials (FSDPX) and Fidelity Select Defense & Aerospace (FSDAX), for astute investors looking to capitalize on these trends.

articles.headline: Top 5 Stocks To Own In 2026: Dan Niles Bets On Apple, Cisco, Boeing And More
articles.summary: Tech investor Dan Niles has identified his top 5 stocks for 2026, predicting a "choppy" market later in the year but significant upside in turnaround stories and overlooked tech plays. His picks include Apple and Cisco for tech, and Boeing and Nike as turnaround opportunities. Niles forecasts an Apple resurgence due to AI and foldable iPhones, and sees Boeing benefiting from regulatory clearance and Nike in a valuation disconnect with recovering North American revenues.

articles.headline: Citigroup (C) Signals Stabilizing Core Businesses and Progress on Strategic Streamlining
articles.summary: Citigroup (NYSE: C) reported strong Q4 2025 results, with an earnings beat driven by a significant recovery in investment banking and corporate client activity. The company's adjusted earnings per share reached $1.81, surpassing the $1.67 consensus, fueled by a 35% surge in investment banking fees. Strategically, Citigroup is progressing with streamlining its footprint, including the sale of its Russian unit, and anticipates that regulatory progress and cost discipline will help close its valuation gap with peers.

articles.headline: Schwab Net Revenue Misses Estimates Amid Strong Year for Markets
articles.summary: Charles Schwab Corp. reported fourth-quarter net revenue of $6.34 billion, which fell short of analysts' estimates of $6.37 billion, despite a strong market year. However, adjusted earnings per share matched projections at $1.39, and net new assets significantly exceeded expectations, reaching $158.2 billion compared to the $144 billion projected.

articles.headline: McDonald's Big Arch Premium Burger And Expansion Refresh Growth Story
articles.summary: McDonald's is launching a new premium burger called the Big Arch and aggressively expanding into new markets, aiming to capture higher-end demand while maintaining its value-focused customer base. These strategies, combined with its global brand and franchise network, are expected to drive growth, building on multi-year share price gains. Investors are advised to monitor customer adoption of the Big Arch and the success of new market openings.

articles.headline: Braskem (NYSE:BAK) Downgraded to "Hold" Rating by Zacks Research
articles.summary: Zacks Research has downgraded Braskem (NYSE:BAK) from "strong-buy" to "hold," with several other firms also cutting ratings, leading to a consensus "Reduce" rating and a target price of $4.40. Despite beating recent quarterly EPS and revenue estimates, analysts anticipate a negative full-year EPS of -0.77. The company's shares opened at $3.05, trading near its 50- and 200-day moving averages, and institutional investors have recently adjusted their holdings.

articles.headline: Watch Gap Inc. CEO Richard Dickson on Sustainability
articles.summary: Gap Inc. CEO Richard Dickson discusses the company's commitment to sustainability, particularly its "Jet Blue" initiative with Matt Damon and Water.org, aimed at addressing the global water crisis. He emphasizes that purpose and profit are intertwined, and highlights how the brand's focus on quality, value, and authentic storytelling has led to consistent sales growth across its brands, even amidst economic headwinds like tariffs. Dickson acknowledges that while Davos conversations might lean more transactional, Gap integrates sustainability as a core business strategy, recognizing nature's economic importance.

articles.headline: Morgan Stanley Remains Bullish on Bank of America (BAC) Following Strong Q4 Results
articles.summary: Morgan Stanley reiterated its 'Overweight' rating on Bank of America (BAC) despite reducing its price target, following the bank's strong Q4 2025 results that beat EPS and revenue expectations. The firm noted a share price drop due to management's expected tightening of the expense ratio and an accounting change complicating comparisons, but highlighted Q4 trading strength and net interest income growth. Bank of America's management anticipates continued NII growth for Q1 and the full year 2026, driven by loan growth and easing deposit costs.

articles.headline: Regions Financial (NYSE:RF) Lowered to Hold Rating by Keefe, Bruyette & Woods
articles.summary: Keefe, Bruyette & Woods downgraded Regions Financial (NYSE:RF) from "moderate buy" to "hold" following the bank's miss on Q4 earnings and revenue estimates. Despite the miss, the company's revenue was up 5.8% year-over-year, and its board authorized a $3.0 billion stock repurchase plan, indicating management believes the stock is undervalued. Regions Financial currently has an average "Hold" rating from analysts with a consensus target price of $29.27.

articles.headline: Barrick Gold Stock: Capitalizing on a Historic Precious Metals Surge
articles.summary: Barrick Gold Corporation is well-positioned to benefit from current record gold prices and increased safe-haven demand amidst geopolitical uncertainty. The company has also resolved a long-standing dispute with the government of Mali, removing a significant operational overhang and stabilizing production. With favorable macroeconomic conditions and strong technical momentum, Barrick Gold is attracting institutional capital as a proxy for direct gold ownership.

articles.headline: Construction bill for BHP's Jansen potash mine in Saskatchewan up by another US$1 billion
articles.summary: The cost for BHP Group Ltd.'s Jansen potash mine in Saskatchewan has increased by US$1 billion, bringing the first stage's price tag to US$8.4 billion, a US$2.7 billion increase from the original US$5.7 billion. Despite these overruns, the company views Jansen as a long-term growth asset, with first production now anticipated in mid-2027 instead of mid-2026. Experts suggest the cost hike is likely due to unexpected engineering hurdles rather than inflation, though it may extend the payback period and potentially delay future expansions.

articles.headline: Brink’s Stock Under Scrutiny: Is BCO’s Latest Pullback a Buying Chance or a Warning Signal?
articles.summary: Brink's Company stock has experienced a slight downturn recently after a strong multi-month performance, prompting investors to question if it's a buying opportunity or a warning sign. Despite the recent dip, the company's fundamentals remain steady, and analysts are largely optimistic, seeing potential for double-digit upside. The company is actively repositioning itself as a broader secure logistics and services platform, moving beyond traditional armored transportation to incorporate technology-enabled cash management and digital vaulting.

articles.headline: Halliburton shares rise as fourth quarter earnings, revenue beat estimates
articles.summary: Halliburton Company reported strong fourth-quarter earnings and revenue that exceeded analyst expectations, leading to a 2% rise in its shares. The oilfield services provider posted adjusted earnings of $0.69 per share and revenue of $5.7 billion, driven by international segment growth. CEO Jeff Miller expressed satisfaction with the company's performance, highlighting its resilient strategy.
